    <!-- Usage Guidelines -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-border dark:border-gray-700">Usage Guidelines</h3>
      <div class="p-6 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg shadow-md">
        <h4 class="font-semibold mb-4">When to use each palette</h4>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div>
            <h5 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-secondary">Secondary Color Palette</h5>
            <ul class="space-y-3 list-disc pl-5">
              <li><strong>Secondary (default):</strong> Use for secondary action buttons, supporting UI elements, and informational components.</li>
              <li><strong>Light variant:</strong> Use for less prominent elements, backgrounds of secondary sections, and subtle highlights.</li>
              <li><strong>Dark variant:</strong> Use for more prominent secondary elements that need stronger contrast.</li>
              <li><strong>Best paired with:</strong> Primary colors for UI hierarchy, or with accent colors for interactive elements.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div>
            <h5 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-accent">Accent Color Palette</h5>
            <ul class="space-y-3 list-disc pl-5">
              <li><strong>Accent (teal):</strong> Use for highlights, success indicators, and tertiary actions.</li>
              <li><strong>Accent warm:</strong> Use for attention-grabbing elements, promotional content, and calls to action that should stand out.</li>
              <li><strong>Light/Dark variants:</strong> Use when you need a more subtle or more prominent version of the accent color.</li>
              <li><strong>Best paired with:</strong> Primary or secondary colors as the main UI structure, with accent colors used sparingly for emphasis.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <h4 class="font-semibold mt-6 mb-4">Accessibility Considerations</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-3 list-disc pl-5">
          <li>Always use the appropriate text color (<code>textOnSecondary</code>, <code>textOnAccent</code>, etc.) to ensure sufficient contrast for readability.</li>
          <li>For interactive elements, ensure that hover and focus states are clearly distinguishable from the default state.</li>
          <li>When using accent colors, especially the warm accent, be mindful of their use for error states or critical actions to avoid confusion.</li>
          <li>Test color combinations in both light and dark modes to ensure proper contrast and visibility.</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h4 class="font-semibold mt-6 mb-4">Color Combination Recommendations</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-3 list-disc pl-5">
          <li><strong>Primary + Secondary:</strong> Use primary for main actions and branding, with secondary for supporting elements and actions.</li>
          <li><strong>Secondary + Accent:</strong> Use secondary for main structure and accent for highlights and interactive elements.</li>
          <li><strong>Primary + Accent Warm:</strong> Creates a strong contrast that can be effective for promotional content or important notifications.</li>
          <li><strong>Avoid:</strong> Using too many accent colors together, or using secondary and accent colors without clear hierarchy, which can create visual confusion.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
